Class UnorderedArrayMaxPQ<Key extends java.lang.Comparable<Key>>

java.lang.Object
UnorderedArrayMaxPQ<Key>
public class UnorderedArrayMaxPQ<Key extends java.lang.Comparable<Key>>
extends java.lang.Object
The UnorderedArrayMaxPQ class represents a max priority queue of generic items. It supports the usual insert and deleteMax operations, along with methods for peeking the max item, testing if the queue is empty.

This implementation uses a resizing array, which double the underlying array when it is full and halves the underlying array when it is one-quarter full. The delMax operation takes linear time. The insert, max, size, and is-empty operations takes constant time in the worst case.
